quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  32,21,"We will certainly make them taste some minor punishment<sup>7</sup> prior to the greater punishment<sup>8</sup>, so that they may return.","[7] i.e., the calamities and trials in this world.\n [8] In the Hereafter."
  32,22,"Who does greater wrong than one who is reminded of the verses of his Lord, then turns away from them? We will surely take vengeance upon the wicked.",""
  32,23,"We gave Moses the Scripture, so do not doubt about meeting him<sup>9</sup>, and We made it a guide for the Children of Israel.","[9] i.e., so do not doubt, O Muhammad, about meeting Moses on the night of al-Mi‘rāj (ascent)."
  32,24,"We made some of them leaders<sup>10</sup>, guiding by Our command, because they observed patience and firmly believed in Our signs.","[10] i.e., prophets and religious leaders."
  32,25,"Indeed, it is your Lord Who will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection concerning that over which they used to differ.",""
  32,26,"Is it not yet clear to them how many generations We destroyed before them, in whose dwellings they now walk about? Indeed, there are signs in this. Do they not then listen?",""
  32,27,"Do they not see that We drive water to parched land, producing thereby crops of which their cattle and they themselves eat? Do they not then see?",""
  32,28,"They say, “When will this Decision<sup>11</sup> be if you are truthful?”","[11] i.e., judgment on the Day of Resurrection."
  32,29,"Say, “On the Day of Decision the belief of those who disbelieved will not benefit them, nor will they be given any respite.”",""
  32,30,"So turn away from them and wait; they too are waiting.",""
